external_knowledge:
- 'Step Master' badge: A badge awarded to users who consistently achieve high step counts;
- 'Marathon runners': Metaphor for users who travel significantly more than the average;
- 'Average daily journey': The mean distance traveled per day;
- 'Average of all travelers': The overall mean distance traveled by all users in the `activity_data` table.

- "Top 3 in their respective challenges" refers to the users who have the highest ranks in the challenge leaderboard for each challenge;
- "Top 5 for both the steps they've taken and the distance they've covered" refers to users who are in the top 5 when ranked by total steps and total distance;
- "Overall performance" is the sum of total steps and total distance.

- 'Top performers' refers to the users with the highest total steps;
- 'Unit system' refers to the preference of measurement (e.g., metric, imperial);
- 'Rewards' are given to the top 3 ranked users in each unit system, with specific names: 'Golden Sneaker' for 1st place, 'Silver Medal' for 2nd place, and 'Bronze Trophy' for 3rd place.

- "Active" refers to users who have taken more than 5000 total steps;
- "Goal-oriented" refers to users who have set at least one goal;
- "Badge-earning" refers to users who have earned at least one badge;
- "Adults" refers to users who are over the age of 18;
- "Notifications turned on" refers to users who have their notification preference set to true (1).

- 'Top performers' refers to users with the highest activity rank (rank = 1) in the challenge arena;
- 'Vibrant activity level' refers to the average activity level of the users;
- 'Challenge arena' refers to the different types of challenges the users participate in.

- 'High activity days' are calculated as the average number of days a user has high activity levels;
- 'Achieved goals' refers to the number of goals a user has completed;
- 'Total goals' is the total number of goals a user has set;
- 'Average challenge score' is the mean score a user has achieved in challenges;
- 'Highest challenge score' is the maximum score a user has achieved in any challenge.

- "the garden of health" refers to the context of user activity and health tracking;
- "walkers" refers to users who have recorded steps in the activity data;
- "the first month of the new year" refers to January 2023;
- "more than a fleeting step" means they have taken more than zero steps.

sql:
SELECT challenge_name, challenge_value
FROM challenges
WHERE challenge_value > (SELECT AVG(challenge_value) FROM challenges);

